@Oso: I didn't notice at the time.  When I looked at the Tangion votes all names but Tangion's were bolded in the OP, for all I know IS could have confirmed by PM already.<br>
<br>
That sounds like you're just going to sit on your ass all game if you're going to ignore questions from player's of unknown alignments.  Everyone is of an unknown alignment.<br>
<br>
@Tebow: I think those votes on Tangion are more likely to come from scum, but of course is only a very minor tell.  This is just because voting for someone who can't/won't react won't get any more useful information into the town, especially at these early stages when that's almost all we have.

@Guttersnipe: I looked up that thread, and it looks like half of it is missing?<br>
<br>
Tebow's reaction to IS's attacks seems very scummy to me, especially the accusation that IS isn't scumhunting.

@Tebow<br>
I would kill McStab.<br>
<br>
@Fate<br>
I agree with your scumread on Code_X, but why is McStab town?

Before I even consider getting on any of these wagons, I want to hear some answers from a few players to some questions that are pretty relevant given the playstyles I've seen here:<br>
<br>
@ChaosOmega: Why do you think Tebow is town? Have you ISO'd him or considered him possibly being scum at this point? You've provided reasons for why other players are town, but not so much for Tebow, and yet you seem to consider him conf. town from your behaviour.<br>
<br>
@Tebow: What do you think about ChaosOmega being scummy? What do you think about the people on his wagon?<br>
<br>
@IS: What do you think about Guttersnipe? <br>
<br>
@Guttersnipe: What do you think about IS?

I tend to think 'I post once a day' is not a statement of choice.  Read it more as 'I go online once a day' than 'I go online several times, but choose not to post on most of them.'  Regardless, it's consistent with his behavior across the site in the last couple weeks.<br>
<br>
@Fitz: Could you explain why you think IS is a good candidate to be <div style="display:inline;font-style:italic">scum</div>?  All you said on him is that his not voting was 'weird' and his push on Chaos has 'gotten old.'

@ChaosOmega: I am aware I have been posting elsewhere on the site. My big catch-up posts take longer than other people's (see Newbie 1255 where this same thing is happening) but I have been reading and keeping up on discussion here. Would you rather I post itty-bitty fluffy posts or get everything I've been thinking out in one great gob so it's easier for you all to respond to? This is not a rhetorical question, it's for future reference.<br>
<br>
Another reason why I've preferred not to post much here is because the exchange between you and Tebow and your accusers is not really something I'm inclined to take part in having not even published my previous reads on the situation in general.

@ChaosOmega: Also, is this more helpful? <br>
<br>
Deadline is in <span class="countdown">(expired on 2012-07-18 08:30:00)</span>. (That's a countdown, have fun.)

@havingfitz: I can't make it all official like Iknal, but the countdown in post 423 is at least accurate to 8:30 A.M. Australian EST.<br>
<br>
@Arugula: *winces at the thought of saying this, but* I think McStab actually makes a valid point here...I'd like to hear about your reluctance to switch from Code_X along with the reasoning behind your reservations about a ChaosOmega lynch. Right now it could go either way (CO or McS), so I'm more interested in hearing about ChaosOmega since he's the one I don't have as much of a grasp of yet. Interested to see what you've got to say...<br>
<br>
@Guttersnipe: I've read and understood your argument, but since it's nearing deadline would you consider doing a favor? I think it would be beneficial to the town, or at least to me, if you and others targeting ChaosOmega laid out your reasoning - plain and simple and updated to fit the current situation. I feel a little tunnelly right now focusing on McStab but I don't have enough of a read on Chaos at this point. Since you all seem so intent to push a Chaos lynch, or at least throw suspicion his way, what have you guys got to say that might convince me to change my vote?<br>
<br>
<div style="display:inline;font-weight:bold"><div style="display:inline;text-decoration:underline">P-EDIT: DID YOU JUST HAMMER AFTER A COPCLAIM?!? You better freakin' hope he was lying or else you're up next tomorrow Guttersnipe.</div></div>

@ChaosOmega: I know, I corrected myself in 457. Regardless of whether he quickhammered before or after the claim, I still find it highly suspect at worst and highly stupid at best.<br>
<br>
@Arugula: That's why I said <div style="display:inline;text-decoration:underline">if McStab flips cop</div> I will be pushing for a Guttersnipe lynch. Nowhere do I say auto-lynch, in fact I've said I'm open to Chaosomega tomorrow. I've still been working on my big reads post so some of my thought process will be in there. I agree that McStab may be jerking us around and I personally believe it's more likely that McStab will flip scum or I wouldn't have voted for him.I was just expressing concern about the lynchflip by saying that if Guttersnipe came out of D1 having quickhammered a/the cop that I wouldn't be happy about it. Would you?

@Guttersnipe: Please read my previous posts where I say I will be finishing a reads post over the game's N1 and D2 and then posting it D2. If that was not explicitly stated, which I thought it was, it was heavily inferred when ChaosOmega and I first discussed the "giant post I've been promising." Also, what does LaL stand for?<br>
<br>
@Tebow: I've been wondering the same thing. I don't think we have 3 scum either, but I was willing to let others keep discussing the possibility since I thought it might give some insight into the knowledge people had of the setup. I originally thought that, balance-wise, it was more likely that we had 2 scum and an SK or Vig...but I don't tihnk that's at all likely after a single NK.

@havingfitz: I'm less comfortable with the possibility of a player who quickhammers town D2 and pushes for a quicklynch right out of the gate D3. Do you blame me?<br>
<br>
Can anybody else honestly say that they think it's likely that scumIS would make the above post?

So IS is at L-1 and he is still here.  If there were two scum left it would already be game over (unless any of you think IS and I are both scum) so I think that pretty much proves there is only 1 left.  <br>
<br>
@Maestro....if you thought my vote on Fate was a quickhammer you weren't paying attention.  I'd reiterate my position from yesterday but I'm sure you can see for yourself with a quick ISO.

I'm going to be voting Chaos as well, but I'm in the middle of a reread right now.<br>
<br>
@Chaos: The least you could do is show some remorse after we lynched town D3...no need to keep bashing the guy when he can't respond.

@Aru: Let me know what you got on your reread. From what I can see, this is part of what put Chaos on IS's radar, so to speak. Remember him wanting Chaos dead for the longest time? It started with the Tebow sheeping early on but I think Chaos started to recede from the pressure and the limelight as soon as he knew he could get away with lurking his way out of situations like that early bus and IS's constant scrutiny.<br>
<br>
On another note, I realized just how few posts you and I have made this game compared to the more active players (e.g. IS, Tebow, Guttersnipe)...but relatively speaking we still had more than Chaos. And no Chaos, if you're going to say I'm "bringing up this point just to encourage your lynch," I'm not. I'm only presenting it as something to consider - especially if you were thinking of denying lurking to a degree during this game.

Perfectly confident, yes Aru. Sorry if that's unsettling, but your as freakin' obvtown to me as humanly possible so this is the only alternative to me. I've been in LyLo once before as town and never as scum, but in the previous situation it was all on me to decide who won - the other two crossvoted and I went the wrong way with my vote. I'm not going to be that person this time so whichever of you votes first, I am going to be voting Chaos and the last one can decide if that's what it comes down to.<br>
<br>
@Chaos: Relying on gut in LyLo is usually not a good idea Chaos, also your sarcasm did not go unnnoticed. Also most of Aru's 758 is WIFOM but I'm leaving it be because it sounds just like the kind of WIFOM that townAru would put down whilst reviewing the game, and I'm guessing that's exactly what it is.

@Oso: Had fun replacing you, shoutout to our scumbuddy McStab for letting me buss him into infinity.<br>
<br>
P-Edit @Axxle: Yeah, I actually did pick up on that. One single post made me kill you during the night, on a hunch that you were PR claiming: <a href="http://forum.mafiascum.net/viewtopic.php?p=4193910#p4193910" class="postlink">http://forum.mafiascum.net/viewtopic.ph ... 0#p4193910</a> ...and I guess that's exactly what it was...?
